				 Rs 4-lakh sympathy for top cop
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Nov. 29: Three of Delhis senior-most IPS officers hopped into a special BSF aircraft yesterday to have tea at the Uttar Pradesh police chiefs home in Lucknow, running up a Rs 4-lakh flight bill for the government.																								Sources said the chiefs of the BSF, CBI and the CISF wanted to lift the mood of their friend, beleaguered by the recent court blasts in the state.																								The occasion was the at home high tea hosted by the state director-general of police, Vikram Singh, as part of the formal celebrations on Uttar Pradesh Police Day. The state has also been observing the Uttar Pradesh Police Week.																								The sources said it was not customary for the chiefs of the three central agencies to attend state police functions. 																								They added that the use of BSF aircraft to attend such a function was unprecedented.																								However, BSF director-general Ashish Kumar Mitra, CISF director-general Ranjeet Kumar Das and CBI director Vijay Shankar  all of them from the Uttar Pradesh cadre are said to be good friends with Singh.																								The CISF and BSF director-generals are batchmates. The CBI director is a year senior, belonging to the 1969 batch. Vikram Singh (1974 batch) is junior to them, but the four of them share a great camaraderie, a source said. 
